The paper deals with reasoning about strategic capabilities of agents in a system, which falls under the category of logic and artificial intelligence (cs.LO, cs.AI). It specifically focuses on uniform memoryless strategies, which is a concept in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses model checking, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions a BDD-based framework, which is a data structure used in programming language theory (cs.PL).
